Gus @GusKenworthy before I was a photographer, I was an amateur snowboarder. I competed on the East Coast circuit. I never met another gay person in the halfpipe. When I photographed Gus, an Olympic skier who came out on ESPN a few years ago, I felt seen. Gus made history for being the first Out athlete at the Olympics. It was a real honor to take his portrait. @ryanmcginleystudios @abercrombie

Support Reproductive Rights! Last Day to view ‘Abortion is Normal’ an Emergency Exhibition at Arsenal Contemporary (214 Bowery NYC) Today is a day of readings, performances & conversations at the gallery. This show is an urgent call-to-action exhibition to raise both awareness and funding in support of accessible, safe, and legal abortion. This show comes at a time when legal abortion is under acute attack throughout the United States.

Abortion is Normal is an Emergency Exhibition [Part II] opens at Arsenal Contemporary (214 Bowery NYC) tonight Tues Jan 21st from 6-8pm 
The show is an urgent call-to-action exhibition to raise both awareness and funding in support of accessible, safe, and legal abortion. This show comes at a time when legal abortion is under acute attack throughout the United States. 
Artists include Ameya Marie Okamoto, Amy Khoshbin, Cajsa von Zeipel, Carrie Mae Weems, Cecily Brown, Chloe Wise, Christopher Myers, Delano Dunn, Elektra KB, Fin Simonetti, Grace Graupe Pillard, Hank Willis Thomas, hayv Kahraman, Jack Pierson, Jaishri Abichandani, Jane Kaplowitz, Jonathan Lyndon Chase, Laurie Simmons, Marilyn Minter, Marisa Morán Jahn, Miguel Luciano, Mika Rottenberg, Narcissister, Portia Munson, Sahana Ramakrishnan, Sarah Sze, Shirin Neshat, Sojourner Truth Parsons, Suzy Lake, Tatyana Fazlalizadeh, Viva Ruiz/TGFA, Xaviera Simmons, Yvette Molina, Zoe Buckman
